<p class="eyebrow"><a href="/docs/api/">API reference</a> / <a href="{{ apiSpecs['v2.2'].urlPath }}">v2.2</a> / Playground</p>
<h1>API playground.</h1>
<p class="lede">Set your VoiceTel API key once. It's encrypted to this device and this browser, never sent to a VoiceTel server, and never readable from this page — only usable. Phase 1 covers GET operations from VoiceTel API v2.2.</p>

<div class="alert alert-info" role="note">
	<p><strong>Your API key never leaves your browser.</strong> The key is encrypted under a non-extractable device key in IndexedDB. Once set, it cannot be viewed here — only used to authorize a request, replaced, or removed.</p>
</div>

<section class="section-block playground" data-api-playground data-spec-url="/api-specs/v2.2.json">
	<header class="playground-header">
		<div class="playground-key">
			<h2>API key</h2>
			<p data-key-status></p>
			<div class="playground-key-actions" data-key-actions></div>
			<form class="playground-key-form" data-key-form hidden autocomplete="off">
				<h3 data-key-form-title>Set API key</h3>
				<p class="form-note">Pasted here, encrypted immediately, then this field is cleared. The plaintext key is never echoed back.</p>
				<div class="form-row form-row--full">
					<label for="playground-key-input">VoiceTel API key</label>
					<input id="playground-key-input" type="password" data-key-input autocomplete="off" spellcheck="false" required>
				</div>
				<p class="form-error" data-key-error></p>
				<div class="form-actions">
					<button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Save</button>
					<button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-key-cancel>Cancel</button>
				</div>
				<p class="form-note">Don't have one? Retrieve your key at <a href="https://api.voicetel.com/apikey/" rel="external">api.voicetel.com/apikey</a>.</p>
			</form>
		</div>
	</header>

	<div class="playground-layout">
		<aside class="playground-sidebar" aria-label="Operations">
			<h2>Operations</h2>
			<div class="playground-op-picker" data-op-picker></div>
		</aside>

		<div class="playground-main">
			<section class="playground-op" aria-labelledby="playground-op-title">
				<header class="playground-op-header">
					<h2 id="playground-op-title" data-op-title>Choose an operation</h2>
					<p class="playground-op-meta" data-op-meta></p>
					<p class="playground-op-summary" data-op-summary></p>
				</header>

				<form class="playground-op-form" data-op-form onsubmit="return false;"></form>

				<div class="playground-actions">
					<button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" data-op-send>Send</button>
				</div>

				<section class="playground-response" aria-label="Response">
					<h3>Response</h3>
					<div data-op-response></div>
				</section>

				<section class="playground-curl" aria-label="curl">
					<div class="playground-curl-header">
						<h3>curl</h3>
						<button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" data-op-copy>Copy</button>
					</div>
					<pre class="code-block" data-lang="bash"><code data-op-curl></code></pre>
					<p class="form-note">The copied command uses the literal string <code>YOUR_API_KEY</code>. Your stored key is never substituted into this preview.</p>
				</section>
			</section>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<aside class="cta-block" aria-labelledby="playground-cta-heading">
	<h2 id="playground-cta-heading">Need to register or rotate a key?</h2>
	<p>API keys are issued at signup and rotated from the portal. The playground only uses keys you already have.</p>
	<p class="hero-actions">
		<a class="btn btn-primary" href="/signup/">Free trial</a>
		<a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/docs/api/v2.2/credentials/">API credentials</a>
	</p>
</aside>
